\"}, {\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4754938952379066e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The South African 4x100m relay team comprised Bayanda Walaza, Benjamin Richardson, Bradley Nkoana and Simbine.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.99919788270548, \"rank\": 0.0006731295369758198, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999605111182029, \"rank\": 3.949043979623771e-05, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"score\": 0.9970532068193869, \"rank\": 0.0027542108065499197, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They crossed the line in a time of 38.08.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, despite the absence of Wayde van Niekerk, the South African 4x400m quartet of Gardeo Isaacs, Zakithi Nene, Matt Nortj\\u00e9 and Lythe Pillay powered their way to a time of 3:00.75 which was good enough to secure a spot in Paris later this year.\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 917, \"